text:
Set in the 1990s, Captain Marvel follows Danvers, an Air Force officer, as she becomes one of the universe's most powerful heroes after earth gets involved in a galactic war between alien. Captain Marvel is a 2019 superhero film directed by Anna Boden and Ryan Fleck and produced by Marvel Studios. It is based on the Marvel Comics character Carol Danvers, played by Brie Larson.
The movie takes place in 1995, during the Kree-Skrull War, with Vers (Brie Larson), a skilled warrior, serving under the command of Yon-Rogg (Jude Law) in the Kree Empire. However, her memories of her past are fragmented and unclear. During a mission to rescue an undercover agent from a Skrull spaceship, Vers encounters a group of Skrulls, led by Talos (Ben Mendelsohn), who probe her mind and reveal flashes of her human life on Earth.
With the help of Nick Fury (Samuel L. Jackson), a young and ambitious S.H.I.E.L.D. agent, Vers escapes and crash-lands on Earth, where she begins to uncover her past identity as Carol Danvers, an Air Force pilot who gained incredible powers after absorbing the energy of a destroyed alien engine. As she navigates her new surroundings and confronts her adversaries, Vers must come to terms with her dual identities and find a way to stop the war between the Kree and Skrulls.
